title: Gunter eases past WW
text:
Gunter eases past WW Gunter eases past WW 
JERRY POWERS / SPECIAL TO THE HERALD DEMOCRAT — Gunter's Noah Williams (1) bounces outside for yardage during Friday night's District 5-3A (II) game against Whitewright. By Jerry PowersSpecial to the Herald Democrat 
GUNTER — Noah Williams had 75 yards and a pair of touchdowns on nine carries as Gunter defeated Whitewright, 38-6, in District 5-3A (II) action on Friday night. 
Gunter (4-3, 1-1) held Whitewright (2-5, 0-2) to 105 yards and Whitewright’s only touchdown came on a 27-yard blocked punt return by Connor Henderson late in the third quarter. 
Williams started the scoring with a four-yard touchdown run that capped a short 40-yard drive. 
A fumble recovery set Gunter up on its next touchdown, a 24-yard run by Colson Stovall. 
Gunter took a 17-0 lead into halftime as Cameron Hearn kicked a 30-yard field goal with time expiring in the second quarter. 
Edgar Fuentes intercepted Payton Jones early in the third quarter and Gunter capitalized on that opportunity with Trey Carr completing a 38-yard touchdown pass to Jake Whitteker for a 24-0 lead. Carr was 8-of-14 passing for 168 yards and an interception and ran eight times for 40 yards. 
Whitewright’s lone scoring opportunity finally came when Gunter had a punt blocked and Henderson quickly responded picking up the ball and returning it for the touchdown. Jones led Whitewright with 40 yards on 16 carries. 
With 44 seconds left in the third quarter, Gunter finished a 57-yard drive with Cade Leach capping it off from the two-yard line. Gunter finished the scoring with 4:10 remaining in the fourth quarter on a 15-yard rush by Williams.
